HEADWORD: minefield
<hw>minefield</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>a
region in which explosive mines{4} have been placed, especially a region
on land.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <mark>(Fig.)</mark> <def>A
situation in which a simple mistake can have disastrous consequences; a
touchy or dangerous situation requiring great caution; <as>as, the
candidate threaded his way skillfully through a <ex>minefield</ex> of
loaded questions from the audience</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>minelayer</ent>⟦br⟧
